{
  "_source": "Primary structure: UNDRR-ISC Hazard Information Profiles (HIPs) 2025 — 7 of 8 hazard clusters (Extraterrestrial omitted as out of scope for urban climate adaptation). Hazards within clusters draw from C40/Arup Climate Hazard Typology (city-level climate hazards) and Resilient Cities Catalysts (RCC) taxonomy (non-climate acute shocks and slow-onset stresses).",
  "_usage": "hazards.hazards_addressed[].hazard_id and hazard_category",
  "_note": "Restructured in v0.1.1 from C40/Arup-primary to HIPs 2025-primary. Each cluster carries c40_arup_categories[] for legacy crosswalk. Each hazard carries c40_arup_category (the legacy C40/Arup parent), hazard_source ('c40_arup' or 'rcc'), and undrr_terms[] for matching UNDRR-framed source documents. The previous rcc_non_climate and rcc_slow_onset buckets were dissolved — their contents now sit in their proper HIPs clusters (Technological, Societal, Geohazards, Environmental).",
